Package: juliaready
Title: Robust Julia Setup for R Packages
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Sebastian", "Funk", , "sebastian.funk@lshtm.ac.uk",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2842-3406"))
Description: Helper utilities for R packages that call into a Julia
    simulation engine. Provides a small, opinionated API for finding
    the Julia binary, installing required Julia packages, loading
    '.jl' bridge files, and managing lazy initialisation. Uses
    JuliaConnectoR (out-of-process Julia via TCP) under the hood,
    chosen over JuliaCall to structurally avoid the embedded-Julia
    segfaults that otherwise leak into R from libR/libjulia symbol
    interactions, environment poisoning, and Pkg operations.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/sbfnk/juliaready
BugReports: https://github.com/sbfnk/juliaready/issues
